'''Riechedly Guillermo Bazoer''' (born 12 October 1996) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] or [[defensive midfielder]] for Turkish club [[Konyaspor]].<ref>{{WorldFootball.net|riechedly-bazoer}}</ref> Born in the Netherlands, he represents the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]].

== Club career ==
[[File:Dnepr-Ajax (2).jpg|thumb|left|upright|Bazoer playing for Ajax]]

=== Ajax ===
Bazoer joined [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] on a free from rival [[Eredivisie]] club [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] on 16 November 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ajax.nl/Ajax-nieuws/Ajax-nieuwsarchief/Ajax-nieuwsartikel/Bazoer-kiest-vol-overtuiging-voor-Ajax.htm|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130628042310/http://www.ajax.nl/Ajax-nieuws/Ajax-nieuwsarchief/Ajax-nieuwsartikel/Bazoer-kiest-vol-overtuiging-voor-Ajax.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=28 June 2013|title=Bazoer kiest vol overtuiging voor Ajax|publisher=Ajax.nl|date=20 November 2012|access-date=26 June 2013}}</ref> He had been linked with a move to the [[Premier League]] with [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] and [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] being mentioned, but opted to sign with Ajax instead.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/2896/premier-league/2012/11/08/3511508/psv-wonderkid-bazoer-weighs-up-offers-from-arsenal-chelsea|title=PSV wonderkid Bazoer weighs up offers from Arsenal, Chelsea & Manchester City|date=8 November 2012|access-date=26 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ad.nl/ad/nl/1441/Ajax/article/detail/3350966/2012/11/20/Ajax-legt-PSV-talent-Bazoer-vast.dhtml|title=Ajax legt PSV talent Bazoer vast|publisher=AD.nl|date=20 November 2012|access-date=26 June 2013}}</ref> No transfer fee was necessary, as the young defender was under age. However it was declared by the [[KNVB]] that Bazoer would not be eligible for the first team of Ajax until after his 16th birthday.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ad.nl/ad/nl/1433/PSV/article/detail/3350169/2012/11/19/Weglokken-Bazoer-door-Ajax-treft-PSV-hard.dhtml|title=Weglokken Bazoer door Ajax treft PSV hard|publisher=AD.nl|date=19 November 2012|access-date=26 June 2013}}</ref> Unable to make his debut in the 2012–13 season for the first team due to the KNVB ruling, he played for [[Jong Ajax]] in the [[Beloften Eredivisie]], as well as participating in the 2013 [[Copa Amsterdam]] with Ajax A1.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.copa-amsterdam.nl/bazoer-geniet-amsterdam/|title=Bazoer geniet Amsterdam|publisher=Copa-Amsterdam.nl|date=20 May 2013|access-date=26 June 2013|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615070222/http://www.copa-amsterdam.nl/bazoer-geniet-amsterdam/|archive-date=15 June 2013}}</ref>

On 29 June 2013, he made his debut for Ajax during a pre-season friendly against [[Sterk Door Combinatie Putten|SDC Putten]]. Bazoer came on as a second-half substitute, with the match ending in a 4–1 win in favour of Ajax.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ajaxshowtime.com/hoofdnieuws/71380/ajax-wint-magertjes-in-putten.html|title=Ajax wint magertjes in Putten|publisher=Ajax Showtime|date=29 June 2013|access-date=29 June 2013|archive-date=16 February 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150216003345/http://www.ajaxshowtime.com/hoofdnieuws/71380/ajax-wint-magertjes-in-putten.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> Bazoer made his professional debut in the [[Eerste Divisie]] for [[Jong Ajax]], in the team's season opener against [[SC Telstar|Telstar]] on 5 August 2013, a match they won 2–0 in the team's first ever match in the second division of Dutch football.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.voetbalzone.nl/doc.asp?uid=193630|title=Debutant Bazoer: 'De stap naar het eerste elftal wordt hierdoor kleiner'|publisher=Voetbalzone.nl|date=6 August 2013|access-date=8 August 2013}}</ref> On 4 September 2013 it was announced that Bazoer was amongst the 22 players who were registered by [[Frank de Boer]] for Ajax's [[2013–14 UEFA Champions League]] campaign.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.soccernews.nl/news/207685/CL-selectie_Ajax_bekend:_Bazoer_ook_speelgerechtigd|title=CL-selectie Ajax bekend: Bazoer ook speelgerechtigd|publisher=Soccernews.nl|date=4 September 2013|access-date=7 September 2013}}</ref> On 15 February 2015, Bazoer scored his first goal for Ajax in a 4–2 win over [[FC Twente]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thestate.com/2015/02/15/3990119/ajax-beats-twente-4-2-to-stay.html|title=Ajax beats Twente 4–2 to stay 12 points behind leader PSV|publisher=thestate|date=15 February 2015|access-date=15 February 2015|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://archive.today/20150216080906/http://www.thestate.com/2015/02/15/3990119/ajax-beats-twente-4-2-to-stay.html|archive-date=16 February 2015}}</ref> On 19 February 2015, Bazoer made his full European debut in a 1–0 win over [[Legia Warsaw (football)|Legia Warsaw]] in the [[2014-15 Europa League|Europa League]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/021e-0e9aaa8f6b8f-cd867be8cf75-1000--cillessen-ensures-ajax-overcome-legia-onslaught/|title=Cillessen ensures Ajax overcome Legia onslaught|publisher=UEFA|date=19 February 2015|access-date=22 February 2015}}</ref>

===VfL Wolfsburg===
On 14 December 2016, [[VfL Wolfsburg]] announced that Bazoer had signed a contract with the Lower Saxony club through 30 June 2021. The transfer went through in the following Winter Transfer period. The reported transfer fee was 12 million euro.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.kicker.de/12-millionen-euro_wolfsburg-schlaegt-bei-bazoer-zu-666796/artikel |title = 12 Millionen Euro: Wolfsburg schlägt bei Bazoer zu}}</ref> He made his [[VfL Wolfsburg]] debut in the [[Bundesliga]] game versus [[TSG Hoffenheim]] on 12 February 2017.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/matchday/20-match-vfl_wolfsburg-tsg_1899_hoffenheim.jsp?statistics|title=VfL Wolfsburg – TSG Hoffenheim statistics|publisher=Bundesliga|date=12 February 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|archive-date=24 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170224051841/http://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/matchday/20-match-vfl_wolfsburg-tsg_1899_hoffenheim.jsp?statistics|url-status=dead}}</ref>

====Porto (loan)====
On 31 August 2018, Bazoer was loaned to [[Primeira Liga]] side [[FC Porto|Porto]] on one-year loan.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fcporto.pt/en/news/2018-en-bazoer-is-a-dragon|title=Bazoer is a Dragon|publisher=FC Porto|date=31 August 2018|access-date=8 January 2019}}</ref> Bazoer did not feature in any league games for Porto due to injuries and lack of discipline which made him play with [[FC Porto B|B team]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.football-oranje.com/no-second-chance-at-porto-for-bazoer/|title=No second chance at Porto for Bazoer|publisher=footballoranje.com|date=4 January 2019|access-date=8 January 2019|archive-date=14 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190414012814/http://www.football-oranje.com/no-second-chance-at-porto-for-bazoer/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

==== Utrecht (loan) ====
On 7 January 2019, he joined [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]] on loan until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.football-oranje.com/utrecht-sign-bazoer-on-loan/|title=Utrecht sign Bazoer on loan|publisher=Football Oranje|date=7 January 2019|access-date=8 January 2019|archive-date=3 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403203104/http://www.football-oranje.com/utrecht-sign-bazoer-on-loan/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

=== Vitesse ===
On 12 July 2019, he joined Vitesse on a permanent transfer from VfL Wolfsburg for an undisclosed amount. He signed a three-year deal.{{citation needed|date=April 2024}} Bazoer made his debut for Vitesse on 3 August 2019 against former club Ajax. In the match, he scored a goal to put Vitesse ahead 2–1 before being sent off for two yellow cards as they were held to a 2–2 draw. On 24 October 2019, Bazoer was left out of the Vitesse squad until further notice due to his attitude.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vitesse.nl/nl/nieuws/detail/8154/bazoer-tot-nader-order-niet-bij-selectie|title=Vitesse nieuws: Bazoer tot nader order niet bij selectie|last=Vitesse|website=Vitesse.nl|language=nl|access-date=24 October 2019}}</ref>

Under head coach [[Thomas Letsch]], Bazoer would grow into a key player. The German manager of Vitesse positioned Bazoer in the position of [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]], after advice by assistant coach [[Joseph Oosting]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lammers |first1=Lex |title=Deze man is bij Vitesse het brein achter coach Letsch, en de uitvinder van de 'Bazoer-constructie' |url=https://www.gelderlander.nl/vitesse/deze-man-is-bij-vitesse-het-brein-achter-coach-letsch-en-de-uitvinder-van-de-bazoer-constructie~ae2b32e8/ |access-date=27 January 2021 |work=De Gelderlander |date=15 January 2021 |language=Dutch}}</ref> As Vitesse finished 4th in the league table in the [[2020–21 Eredivisie|2020–21 season]], Bazoer was voted "Player of the Season" by Dutch football magazine ''[[Voetbal International]]''.<ref>{{cite news |title=Bazoer blijft Wijndal en Tadic voor en is VI Speler van het Jaar |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/bazoer-blijft-wijndal-en-tadic-voor-en-is-vi-speler-van-het-jaar |work=Voetbal International |date=17 May 2021 |language=nl}}</ref>

=== AZ Alkmaar ===
On 1 August 2022, Bazoer joined [[AZ Alkmaar|AZ]] on a free transfer, signing a three-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=1 August 2022 |title=AZ contracteert Bazoer |trans-title=AZ hirez Bazoer |url=https://www.az.nl/nl/nieuws/az-contracteert-bazoer |access-date=1 August 2022 |website=www.az.nl |language=dutch |archive-date=2 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220802083152/https://www.az.nl/nl/nieuws/az-contracteert-bazoer |url-status=dead }}</ref>

=== Konyaspor ===
On 11 September 2024, Bazoer signed a two-year contract with [[Konyaspor]] in Turkey.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Konyaspor|url=https://www.konyaspor.org.tr/Haber/hos-geldin-riechedly-bazoer/9642|title=Hoş geldin Riechedly Bazoer|trans-title=Welcome Riechedly Bazoer|date=11 September 2024|access-date=4 October 2024|language=tr}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
Bazoer has represented the Netherlands at various youth levels. He participated in the [[2012 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]], helping to contribute to the [[Netherlands national under-17 football team|Netherlands]]' second consecutive continental title in that age group by defeating [[Germany national under-17 football team|Germany]] 5–4 on penalties in the final, after extra time following a 1–1 deadlock.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onsoranje.nl/nieuws/artikel/12326/onder-17-europees-kampioen|title=Onder 17 Europees Kampioen|publisher=Onsoranje.nl|date=16 May 2012|access-date=26 June 2013|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121107032146/http://onsoranje.nl/nieuws/artikel/12326/onder-17-europees-kampioen|archive-date=7 November 2012}}</ref>

On 4 January 2013, the [[Curaçao Football Federation]] expressed an interest in calling up Bazoer to represent the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao U-20]] team for the [[2013 CONCACAF U-20 Championship]] in Mexico.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.concacaf.com/page/ConfederationDetail/0,,12813~2730083,00.html|title=U-20 finals set for Mexico, U-17s to Panama|publisher=CONCACAF.com|date=4 November 2012|access-date=26 June 2013|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120413211011/http://www.concacaf.com/page/ConfederationDetail/0,,12813~2730083,00.html|archive-date=13 April 2012}}</ref> Bazoer was eligible due to his age and heritage, and this would not have conflicted with his decision to play for the Netherlands given the player's age but the offer was turned down by his agents, and Bazoer remained in Amsterdam.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://curacaosport.com/voetbalbond-hoopt-op-riechedly-bazoer/|title=Voetbalbond hoopt op Riechedly Bazoer|publisher=Curaçao Sport|date=4 January 2013|access-date=23 June 2013|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615080609/http://curacaosport.com/voetbalbond-hoopt-op-riechedly-bazoer/|archive-date=15 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ajaxf-side.nl/shownews.asp?id=25454|title=Curaçao hoopt Bazoer te strikken voor kwalificatie-toernooi WK bij ontbreken dispensatie|publisher=Ajax F-Side.nl|date=3 January 2013|access-date=26 June 2013}}</ref>

===Senior===
====Netherlands====
[[File:20160604 AUT NED 8873.jpg|thumb|207x207px|Bazoer with the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] in 2016]]
Bazoer received his first call up to the senior [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands team]] in October 2015 to replace the injured [[Davy Klaassen]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Klaassen, Promes withdrawn from Dutch squad|url=http://www.fourfourtwo.com/sg/news/klaassen-promes-withdrawn-dutch-squad#:f8dWVfUiiC9ZIA|access-date=11 October 2015|publisher=football-oranje.com|date=5 October 2015|archive-date=6 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306211645/http://www.fourfourtwo.com/sg/news/klaassen-promes-withdrawn-dutch-squad#:f8dWVfUiiC9ZIA|url-status=dead}}</ref> and again on 6 November 2015 for friendlies against [[Wales national football team|Wales]] and [[Germany national football team|Germany]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fourfourtwo.com/news/blind-calls-depay-dutch-squad-retains-robben#:TWF067YhWgTrsA|title=Blind calls Depay into Dutch squad, retains Robben|date=2 November 2015|publisher=fourfourtwo.com|access-date=6 November 2015}}</ref> He made his senior debut as a late substitute against Wales on 13 November 2015.<ref>{{cite news|title=Wales 2–3 Netherlands|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34742189|access-date=14 November 2015|publisher=BBC|date=13 November 2015}}</ref> He was called up to the preliminary squad for the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]] for the [[2021 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref name=":0">{{cite web|date=18 June 2021|title=2021 Concacaf Gold Cup preliminary rosters announced|url=https://www.concacaf.com/gold-cup/article/2021-concacaf-gold-cup-preliminary-rosters-announced/|access-date=19 June 2021|publisher=CONCACAF}}</ref>

On 29 August 2025, Bazoer's request to [[List of association football players capped by two senior national teams|change]] sports citizenship from Dutch to Curaçaoan was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://knowledge.fifa.com/change-of-association-platform|title=FIFA Change of Association Platform|website=knowledge.fifa.com|date=29 August 2025|accessdate=29 August 2025}}</ref>

====Curaçao====
Bazoer made his senior [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao]] debut on 5 September 2025 in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – CONCACAF third round|2026 World Cup qualifier]] match against [[Trinidad and Tobago national football team|Trinidad and Tobago]] ending a 0–0 draw.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.sofascore.com/football/match/curacao-trinidad-and-tobago/mdcsCqx |title=Trinidad and Tobago v Curaçao|date=5 September 2025|work=[[Sofascore|Sofascore.com]]|access-date=6 September 2025}}</ref>

